snippet.textDisplay: The 8 rib belt is from the factory, Ford updated the pulleys after all the issues during the terminator program. If the plugs on 4 and 8 are damaged keep an eye on them, you might have an issue in the tune. Ford turns 8 down as the cooling system cannot efficiently remove the heat on that cylinder as cyl 8 is at the end of the cooling system. This issue is why there are colant crossover kits for mod motors. Just a heads up so you dont have a costly failure.

snippet.textDisplay:
I bought a 1992 300zx twin turbo from a guy I used to work with. He wanted 6500 for it. I got a cashiers check and drove my 1988 300zx JWT turbo down to test drive the car. I drove the TT with him and I asked if he was sure it was a twin turbo because my 88 T pulled harder. I pulled the TT over to make sure that it was a TT. It was and it also had the TT wing.
I knew something was not right but the turbos were not smoking and it was not skipping. The boost gauge didn't work either but since I had bought the 1988 300zx automatic N/A and I changed it to a turbo 5 speed using a donor car, I knew what ever was wrong, I could fix on the TT. I drove it on to work and took another coworker for a ride and I told him something was wrong.
The next day I checked the fuel filter and it was clogged bad. I changed it and it was much better but I knew it wasn't running right. I checked the detonation sensor because detonation will put it in safety boost. I went to radio shack and bought a 1 million ohm resister to put in the det sensor connector to bypass it, and the car came alive big time. I took the same guy that rode in it before I fixed it and he couldnt believe how much faster it was. He asked me what was wrong when I bought it and how much it cost me to fix it. I told him about 12 dollars for the FF and 1 dollar for the resistor 13 dollars total. He told the guy I bought it from and he didn't believe me so after work I took the previous owner for a ride and he was sick that he sold it so cheap!

The boost gauge didn't work either but since I had bought the 1988 300zx automatic N/A and I changed it to a turbo 5 speed using a donor car, I knew what ever was wrong, I could fix on the TT. I drove it on to work and took another coworker for a ride and I told him something was wrong. 
   The next day I checked the fuel filter and it was clogged bad. I changed it and it was much better but I knew it wasn't running right. I checked the detonation sensor because detonation will put it in safety boost. I went to radio shack and bought a 1 million ohm resister to put in the det sensor connector to bypass it, and the car came alive big time. I took the same guy that rode in it before I fixed it and he couldnt believe how much faster it was. He asked me what was wrong when I bought it and how much it cost me to fix it. I told him about 12 dollars for the FF and 1 dollar for the resistor 13 dollars total. He told the guy I bought it from and he didn't believe me so after work I took the previous owner for a ride and he was sick that he sold it so cheap!
